spanGrp.span: ‘That child, his mother put [him] into a cylinder.
Je yaba í mina të jiáchá estee nã tarrokwö nã
Then they left and some deer came to see him.
Jemẽ jie-wa mẽnẽu-lo mãĩ mululbe deu í sũã'
He chased them into the woods;
he fell down and when he was going down a snake rolled him up. It took him up a tree.
kã' tiá-ite jemẽ mãĩ damĩu-lo ska kebé të í (_) wö mũliswã'-wã tsá-mĩ kal ba kal bata nã
When his parents came to see him where they had left him, they did not find him; so they went out to search for him.
Í kaga-wa deu-lo í sũã'-ra (_) (_) mãĩ jie-wa të í jiáchã' ska í mẽnẽu-lo í yulö-ra ka wã í kõnẽ
So they lost sight of the child and could not find him.’
jebi yaba shenã'-wã í wö nã Jemẽ ka wã í yaba kõnẽ ĩã
